(402, 'studenttrail03', '                                                                                <h2 style=\"font-size: 24px; line-height: 1.5; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 12px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">Unlock Tomorrow and Embrace the Power of Transdisciplinary Collaboration</h2><p style=\"margin-bottom: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 18px;\">Ever wondered about the magic beyond traditional study boundaries? Welcome to transdisciplinarity – where diverse backgrounds blend to create innovative solutions for societal challenges. Its not like a fruit salad with separate ideas; its a smoothie of different knowledge and perspectives! Explore this space, develop future-proof skills, and embrace transdisciplinary education for a unique learning experience.</p><h2 style=\"font-size: 24px; line-height: 1.5; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 12px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">Collaboration with Different Stakeholders in Transdisciplinary Education</h2><p style=\"margin-bottom: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 18px;\">Transdisciplinary is all about teamwork that tackles real-world issues. Imagine a diverse team of students, professionals, and community members working together to solve problems. More than books and classes; its about collaborating with various ‘real world’ partners and their different perspectives, which make education more hands-on and real. It offers you tools to engage with the complex world and shape a future society.</p><h2 style=\"font-size: 24px; line-height: 1.5; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 12px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">Wicked Problems</h2><p style=\"margin-bottom: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 18px;\">Think about the problems we face in society – theyre not always straightforward, right? Transdisciplinarity dives into these complex, wicked problems and figures out new ways towards solutions. Whether big societal challenges or practical problems, transdisciplinarity is the key. And you – the student – are part of that.</p><h2 style=\"font-size: 24px; line-height: 1.5; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 12px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">Equality</h2><p style=\"margin-bottom: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 18px;\">The cool thing is how everyone in transdisciplinarity collaborates. Its not just about learning or working together; its about creating something new, exploring, and researching together on an equal level. It involves dealing with complex problems and working closely with different people. Its teamwork that tackles the tough stuff in the world and regards you as an equal among all equal team members.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 18px;\">Links:</p><ul style=\"margin-bottom: 16px; padding-left: 20px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 18px;\"><li>Collaborative partners</li><li>Nature of the problem</li><li>Form of engagement</li><li>Common goal</li></ul>                                                                      ', 1, '8', 3),
